duced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Mauleverer was born in 1303, his father, Sir William Mauleverer, was 26 and his mother, Anne de Neville, was 19. He had at least 1 son with Mariot Attwood."},"et":{"1303–":"1303–Surnud","1295–Male":"1295–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1303–Male":"1303–Surnud","1306–Male":"1306–Surnud","1327–Female":"1327–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1297–Female":"1297–Surnud","1277–1352":"1277–1352","1285–1361":"1285–1361","1327":"1327","1303":"1303","1300":"1300","1277":"1277","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1297":"1297","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1295":"1295","1306":"1306","Wodersham, England":"England"},"fi":{"1303–":"1303–Kuollut","1295–Male":"1295–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1303–Male":"1303–Kuollut","1306–Male":"1306–Kuollut","1327–Female":"1327–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1297–Female":"1297–Kuollut","1277–1352":"1277–1352","1285–1361":"1285–1361","1327":"1327","1303":"1303","1300":"1300","1277":"1277","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1297":"1297","1285":"1285","1361":"1361","1295":"1295","1306":"1306","Wodersham, England":"England"},"fr":{"1303–":"1303–Décédé","1295–Male":"1295–Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1303–Male":"1303–Décédé","1306–Male":"1306–Décédé","1327–Female":"1327–Décédée","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1297–Female":"1297–Décédée","1277–1352":"1277–1352","1285–1361":"1285–1361","1327":"1327","1303":"1303","1300":"1300","1277":"1277","1330":"1330","1352":"1352","1297":"1297","1285":